<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870126-0122 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Guardian Savings andamp; Loan Association</HL><DD> 01/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   GUARDIAN SAVINGS andamp; LOAN ASSOCIATION sold $50 million of subordinated debentures due 2002 at 12 5/8% and priced at par, Merrill Lynch Capital Markets, the lead underwriter, said. The Houston-based thrift said it will use proceeds to purchase Government National Mortgage Association certificates. </TEXT></DOC>